Description: LATAM Blockchain Group is a leading the blockchain expansion in Latin America.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: LATAM Blockchain Group is a startup founded by two South American entrepreneurs in order to boost and create a blockchain ecosystem in the region. South American countries are known for falling behind in technological advancements such as the internet and mobile. Blockchain, cryptocurrencies, and DLT technologies offer a more transparent, decentralized, and faster transaction of data and information across borders.  South American citizens have been victims of hyperinflation, corruption, economic disasters and political instability. As with most big tech companies, not so many blockchain projects have set their eyes on the Latin American continent for varied reasons, problems, and resources. We want to change that, thus we believe with education, we will be able to create entrepreneurs, students, and professionals hungry to thrive in this disruptive wave, thus creating an ecosystem of talented individuals to compete with leading countries in the industry and resolve some of South Americans biggest flaws. Latinos have 65% mobile penetration and 55% of its citizens are unbanked. Together with Lumit Blockchain and Blockchain at Berkeley, we launched an online e-learning platform called Academia 21 to educate Latinos about blockchain in Spanish and offer courses for blockchain development, fundamentals, business use cases, smart contracts, token economics, investing, token creation and more. Our vision is to be the gateway of blockchain powered solutions to South American governments and companies within the supply chain management, healthcare, and real estate industries.
Industry Groups: Blockchain and Cryptocurrency, Education, Information Technology, Internet Services, Other

Description: Chapman Innovations develops, produces and markets thermal fabric solutions for a variety of industries and end uses.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Chapman Innovations develops, produces and markets thermal fabric solutions for a variety of industries and end uses. On a daily basis, Chapman’s leading brand, CarbonX® fabrics, protects individuals working in some of the world's most hazardous environments within the industrial, firefighting, motorsports, and tactical markets. No other brand of flame-resistant (FR) fabric or apparel protects professionals working in extreme conditions like CarbonX. With TPP and ATPV ratings far surpassing industry standards, CarbonX significantly outperforms similarly classified FR wear. The superior performance of CarbonX products can be attributed to their high-performance fiber blend. This patented fiber blend provides an extraordinary level of protection and enables their PPE solutions to be optimized for a wide variety of applications. CarbonX products are constructed to be truly non-flammable. They will not burn, melt, drip, ignite, shrink, or char when exposed to direct flame or extreme heat; are highly resistant to molten metal splash, flammable liquids, and certain chemicals; and provide excellent protection from arc flash hazards. Even after intense exposure, CarbonX products maintain their strength and integrity and continue to protect. CarbonX products combine an extreme level of protection with maximum comfort. They are lightweight, soft-to-the-touch, and flexible, wearing much like cotton. They also breathe well, wick away moisture, and dry quickly, enhancing the wearer’s comfort and productivity and reducing the potential for fatigue and heat stress. Because CarbonX products are inherently non-flammable, their thermal protective properties will not wash out or wear away. They have a long wear life and are machine washable and easy to care for. Apparel made of CarbonX fabrics can be worn daily as part of a total PPE solution, providing significant value to users. CarbonX partners with leading safety supply distributors and manufacturers to deliver customized PPE solutions. They work closely with their partners to understand their customers’ needs and then provide solutions to meet those needs. This collaborative approach has led to many innovative product developments and increased business opportunities for their partners. CarbonX also has the advantage of being owned by Tex Tech Industries Inc., a global developer and manufacturer of engineered, high-performance materials. Tex Tech’s worldwide distribution platform and in-house engineering, testing, and manufacturing capabilities enable the development and introduction of new CarbonX products to the market much more quickly.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Government and Military, Manufacturing

Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Motus Integrative Health adjustment is that chiropractors refer to as spinal manipulative therapy. An inflamed and painful joint can regain function and motion by using a velocity, amplitude push combined with a soft but manipulation from the chiropractor. The adjustment activates the neurological system, which helps to relax the local musculature and lessen pain. During an adjustment, some patients may hear a popping noise, similar to they would hear if they cracked their fingers. The discharge of nitrogen gas from a joint capsule causes the popping sound. The professionals at Motus Integrative Health can determine precisely the body is moving and where it might need to move more effectively by carefully evaluating the ranges of motion in various joints.

Description: Professional Training Centers is a school in Miami.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Since 1994, Professional Training Centers (PTC) has been committed to providing a high quality education to students interested in pursuing a career in allied health care.  PTC serves a diverse community in Miami, FL and is dedicated to offering an intellectually stimulating environment through relevant technical training and with an emphasis on critical thinking.  The school offers associates degrees, diploma programs and continued education specifically tailored to the allied health care needs of the community it serves.  Any student considering a career in allied health care at Professional Training Centers should contact the school to speak with an admissions representative. Our admissions representatives are trained to help students consider their options for academic study, as well as helping them complete their applications. Contact the college for more information on the admissions process. The campus at PTC is located in a quiet residential neighborhood surrounded by beautiful parks and lakes. Students with families can benefit from the nearby daycare centers, schools and shopping centers. Comprised of seven buildings, the campus offers student services such as a cafeteria, library and several laboratories. The laboratories are equipped with updated and advanced technologies used by allied health care industry professionals. Each classroom has computers, video projectors and multimedia software to help professors teach the course material in compelling ways. In order to help our students get the most out of their career training, each program requires that they complete an externship at a related health facility. The externship allows students to gain hands-on experience in their fields that is valued by many employers. Students interested in professional development can take advantage of the school's continuing education courses, which allow them to brush up on and update their professional skills. Tuition varies depending on which program a student pursues. To help students who cannot afford the cost of tuition, Professional Training Centers provides a variety of financial aid services. Students who are eligible may apply for financial assistance from the state and federal government. Contact PTC to get more information on obtaining financial aid. Students receive career advisement starting with an initial meeting with the admissions representative and extending through the course of their programs. PTC offers job placement services to all students and alumni, although the school can never guarantee that a student will obtain a job. Available services include resume writing assistance, interviewing techniques, time management skills and job search techniques.

Description: Palo Alto Data is a realtime scale-independent analytics, visualization, search and discovery for the Internet of Things.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Realtime Scale-Independent Analytics, Visualization, Search and Discovery The Internet of Things is creating a growing demand from companies for a new kind of realtime analytics system that can handle sensor data at extreme scale. A single company might need to continuously analyze data from millions of live streams, with terabytes of new data coming in every day. They need realtime actionable insight, enabling them to instantly discover important opportunities and threats, and to respond to them immediately. At Palo Alto Data we’re building the first IoT Intelligence app - an app that enables companies to continuously capture, aggregate and index any number of IoT data streams from fixed or mobile sensors, to visualize, analyze and search the data in realtime, to set custom realtime alerts, and to algorithmically discover and rank important events and patterns automatically. The app is built on industry-standard big data software and cloud services.  It’s massively scalable, super-fast and simple to use. The app can be run on-premise or accessed as a cloud service. Contact us for more information.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Design, Information Technology, Internet Services, Other, Software
